            {
               "id": "conclusion",
               "text": "<p><h3>Conclusion</h3>Entities that can be assembled, grouped, have been emerging in the universe since the earliest moments after its departure from the singularity. These formations have evolved from the smallest particles to colossal structures. In our next session, we will delve further into the formations that facilitated the emergence of life.<p>"
            },
            {
               "id": "exercise_v2",
               "text": [
                  {
                     "question": "Do the universe always had the size we observe?",
                     "yesNoAnswer": "No",
                     "additionalInfo": "For a period of time, the idea of a static universe dominated over other hypotheses. However, Edwin Hubble's measurements, followed by others, confirmed that the universe is expanding."
                  },
                  {
                     "question": "First the matter we cannot see appear, the atoms, and later the matter we see appeared. Is this sentence correct?",
                     "yesNoAnswer": "Yes",
                     "additionalInfo": "The observable structures in the universe are formed from smaller groupings of matter; thus, everything we see is organized from the smallest to the largest."
                  },
                  {
                     "question": "Everything we see comes from a unique place, the singularity, is it possible to say: I have something different of other people?",
                     "yesNoAnswer": "No",
                     "additionalInfo": "Some people mistakenly consider themselves different from others, but everything shares the same origin, whether it’s other humans, other animals, or any other matter around us."
                  }
               ]
            },
